entry.name: Quantitative proteomics time-course experiment of mock vs HIV-1-infected SupT1 cells at 4, 8 and 20 hours postinfection.
entry.description: TRANCHE KEY: xqNw6/dOU2nEqoUoqMg+W1t8AQi2LXrWNLaY/6abuXpMzaCBbrxCAnsuWiKokZKaC75Et1PirlHDhJVkNXK7Ka1uGV4AAAAAAAARaA== Experiment: MERGED_DE-2, data file: MERGED_DE-pool3-2.mgf. From Tranche:{{i}}... Each iTRAQ multiplex experiment was fractionated off-line Strong Cation Exchange SPE cartridges with increasing concentrations (300,400,500,600,and 1000 mM KCl,in 25% acetonitrile,10 mM potassium phosphate monobasic,pH3) of potassium chloride buffer. Fractions 300mM and 400mM were combined into one fraction, and fractions 600mM and 1M were combined into a second fraction before proceeding with the desalting step.The third fraction with 500mM KCl was not combined with the other fractions. Finally,the three KCl fractions were desalted using C18 SPE cartridges. Online peptide separation followed by mass spectrometric analysis was performed on a 1D-nanoLCsystem coupled to a LTQ Orbitrap Velos mass spectrometer. ...{{/i}}
